  <subfield code="o">32</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">At a first glance, eq. (12) may look like dimensionally inconsistent but it is not, because while converting a functional from its discrete to continuous form we must divide the discrete form with a weight factor of dimension the same as that of the continuous variable. In this expression we have used a weight factor of unit length</subfield>
